# Local Setup

Clone the repository:

git clone <repo-url>

Backend setup:

cd backend
npm install
npm run start:dev

Frontend setup:

cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev

---

# Environment Variables

Example `.env`:

MONGODB_URI=
JWT_SECRET=
PORT=3000

Frontend:

NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=

---

# Design Decisions

Next.js was chosen for the frontend due to its built-in routing and seamless Vercel deployment.

NestJS was selected for the backend due to its modular architecture and scalability.

MongoDB Atlas was used as the database to support flexible schema design and easy cloud deployment.

Server-side filtering was implemented to ensure efficient pagination and prevent large data transfers.

---

